headline: Kyndryl beats quarterly revenue estimates on AI push
summary: Companies enhancing their IT systems to incorporate the extensive data and processing needs of AI technology have benefited Kyndryl, which helps businesses manage key data architecture.  "We expanded our capabilities in cloud, modernization, applications, AI and security," Kyndryl CEO Martin Schroeter said in a statement.  Kyndryl's fourth-quarter revenue fell about 1% to $3.80 billion.

headline: IBM Report: Canadian CEOs Embrace AI
summary: Canadian CEOs are making bold strides in the global race to unlock AI's potential, according to the 2025 IBM Institute for Business Value (IBV) CEO Study. Productivity gains are the key driver behind leaders' desire to adopt generative AI, including the ability to automate routine tasks, optimize workflows, analyze data, and provide actionable insights.
